description:
**Location:** Remote


We’re excited to offer a long-term opportunity for an experienced **Manual QA Engineer** to join a team of professional engineers and designers. Together, you’ll be working on a **US-based product** that’s set to make a significant impact on the PropTech scene. This role offers the chance to contribute to a major market and collaborate with top talent in a dynamic environment.

**About ElevateOS Product**

**ElevateOS** has been improving the resident experience for over seven years. We created a single, all-in-one platform that makes it easy for property managers and resident staff to work together. Our goal is simple: to provide the best experience for residents by replacing multiple, confusing apps with one easy solution.


This is a stable, long-term project that continues to grow, and you'll have the chance to be part of its ongoing success.


Our primary technology stack revolves around JavaScript. We use React for the front-end, Node.js for the back-end, and React Native for mobile development.

**What skills are essential to us?**

* 2+ years of experience as a Manual QA Engineer;
* Knowledge and understanding of the development process and software life cycle;
* Knowledge of testing methodologies.
* Proficiency in manual Web/Mobile/API/Requirements testing;
* Familiarity with writing test documentation, requirements review, creating bug reports;
* Understanding certain marking/scripting/programming languages, required for the project (e.g. JSON, XML, HTML/CSS);
* English - upper-intermediate;

*Additional (good-to-have) skills:*

* Experience with Automated testing;
* Experience with CI/CD (Circle.ci, GH Actions);

**What will your responsibilities include?**

* Analysis of requirements, preparing a query list based on those requirements;
* Writing and executing test cases to detect usability and performance issues;
* Conducting exploratory testing – simultaneous tests of design and functionality;
* Verification of multi-device and cross-platform consistency;
* Creating detailed reports and listing improvements;
* Participation in planning meetings and providing feedback to the team;
* Writing documentation;


We are looking forward to having you on board to contribute to our journey of transforming real estate property management!
